âš™ï¸ How It Works (Behind the Scenes)
1. The frontend sends a google_id_token.
2. Laravel verifies the token using Firebase.
3. If the token is valid:
Checks if the user is already in the database.

If not, it creates a new user.

Then it creates a Sanctum access token and refresh token.

4. Sends back a response to the frontend with the tokens.
ğŸ” Security Features
âœ… Sanitization â€“ Cleans up user data like email and name.
âœ… Rate Limiting â€“ Limits how often an IP can hit the endpoint (60 times per minute).
âœ… CORS â€“ Allows frontend apps on different domains to access the API.

ğŸ§ª How to Test It
